{
  "stem": "27770.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The guy was full with blood.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Slowly everybody left the line.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Nobody want to have a soup anymore, because if you get [INAUDIBLE] the soup, to be killed for a soup, and then everybody left the line, not because they wanted to leave, because they was afraid to be killed like this particular Jew.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "The Hungarian said, you see?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We made a soup for nothing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "They are not hungry.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And they took the whole soup and they threw it out, middle of the ghetto on the floor.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "The Germans, they didn't do never such a thing, but the Hungarian that how they started already in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To tell you how bad was in this brick factory, two weeks to be a big factory was worse than to be one year in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I can describe you what was it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then, of course, the trains, they arrived.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In the trains, they was putting in letters, probably a lot of Jews, they're forced to write these letters.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they writing in Jewish words.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We arrived.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It means that this train came already back from one of the shipments, who those first shipment arrived already to this labor camp.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the labor camp is in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They call it, they gave a name [NON-ENGLISH] And we have it fine.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The children and older people are not working, only the men who are capable to work, they do labor work.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "In order to confuse the public that he's not going to Auschwitz, he's not going out from the Hungary, he's staying in [NON-ENGLISH] in the same town whatever it is in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And people believed it.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
